  "note": "Codified from the City of New Braunfels Code of Ordinances, Chapter 144 (Zoning), Article III (Zoning Districts), Sec. 144-3.4 (Zoning districts and regulations for property zoned subsequent to June 22, 1987) — Supplement 36 Update 3, codified through Ordinance No. 2026-26 adopted April 13, 2026 (Municode ProductID 11333, job Id 491608). Source is Municode; every district cites Sec. 144-3.4 (the post-1987 district regulations; the parallel pre-1987 Sec. 144-3.3 set is NOT used here). Each district's 'Height, minimum area and setback requirements' block states dimensions in prose, not a table. MODELING NOTES: (1) 'Front/Rear/Side building setback' map to front_ft/rear_ft/side_ft; the residential 'side setback on corner lots adjacent to the street' maps to side_corner_ft. (2) Several R-1A districts state TWO corner side values (15 ft where corner rear lot lines coincide with adjacent rear lot lines; 25 ft where they coincide with adjacent SIDE lot lines); the 15 ft base is codified and the 25 ft variant is flagged. (3) Chapter 144 states NO per-district maximum building lot-coverage or impervious-cover cap in these sections, so max_lot_coverage_pct and max_impervious_pct are not_specified and carry 100 as non-binding stand-ins. (4) Districts stating 'no side building setback required' except adjacent to residential (C-1A, C-1B, M-1A, M-2A) codify side_ft = 0 with the 6-ft-adjacent-to-residential exception flagged; corner side uses the stated 15 ft where given. (5) TH-A (townhouse) and ZH-A (zero lot line) interior side = 0 by design. (6) R-3L height is '35 feet or 50 feet when a pitched roof is used'; the 35 ft base is codified. (7) APD (agricultural/pre-development), B-1A/B-1B (manufactured home), MU-A/MU-B (form-based mixed use), C-2A (central business, no stated front setback), and C-4A/C-4B (resort) are EXCLUDED as agricultural, incomplete, or form-based without a simple per-district setback set.",
